locks":[{"type":"title","text":"Word List 18 >>>"},{"type":"entry","text":"futility","headword":"futility"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.无用，无益(the quality of being futile)"},{"type":"text","text":"[fju:'tlati]"},{"type":"text","text":"The legislators of 1563 realized the futility of trying to regulate the flow of labor"},{"type":"text","text":"without securing its reasonable remuneration, and so the second part of the"},{"type":"text","text":"statute dealt with establishing wages."},{"type":"entry","text":"dedication","headword":"dedication"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 奉献，献身(devotion to a cause or an aim)"},{"type":"text","text":"[dedr'kerfn]"},{"type":"text","text":"图来自dedicate（v.奉献）"},{"type":"entry","text":"ornate","headword":"ornate"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.华美的(showy or flowery)：充满装饰的(heavily ornamented or adorned)"},{"type":"text","text":"[o:r'nert]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：orn（装饰）+ate→装饰过的→华美的"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 有常识的(having practical judgment gained from experience of life, not by"},{"type":"entry","text":"commonsense","headword":"commonsense"},{"type":"text","text":"['ka:mansens]"},{"type":"text","text":"special study)"},{"type":"text","text":"图组合词：common（普通的）+sense（认识）→具有常识的"},{"type":"entry","text":"redundancy","headword":"redundancy"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.多余，累赞：（因劳动力过剩而造成的）裁员：人浮于事"},{"type":"text","text":"[rr'dandansi]"},{"type":"text","text":"本单词亦作redundance"},{"type":"text","text":"The chances that a species will persist are reduced if any vital function is"},{"type":"text","text":"restricted to a single kind of organ; recuncancy by itself possesses an enormous"},{"type":"text","text":"survival advantage."},{"type":"entry","text":"alert","headword":"alert"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 警惕的,机警的(watchful and prompt to meet danger or emergency) n. 警报"},{"type":"text","text":"[a'l3:rt]"},{"type":"text","text":"(warning)"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：al（去）+ert（高处）→在望塔上观察→警惕的"},{"type":"entry","text":"expenditure","headword":"expenditure"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.花费，支出：支出额（amountexpended）"},{"type":"text","text":"[rk'spendrt{ar]"},{"type":"text","text":"图lavishexpenditure过多的开支"},{"type":"text","text":"喵喵"},{"type":"entry","text":"bewilder","headword":"bewilder"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.使迷感，混乱（to confuse）"},{"type":"text","text":"[br'wrldar]"},{"type":"note","text":"园词根记忆：be（使）+wilder（迷惑）→使迷惑"},{"type":"text","text":"befog. confound, perplex"},{"type":"text","text":"bewilder"},{"type":"text","text":"bewildering（adj令人困感的：令人费解的）"},{"type":"entry","text":"zone","headword":"zone"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 地[区(a section of an area or a territory established for a specific purpose) v. 分"},{"type":"text","text":"[zaun]"},{"type":"text","text":"成区(to divide into or assign to zones)"},{"type":"entry","text":"drawn","headword":"drawn"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 的(showing the effects of tension, pain, or illness)"},{"type":"text","text":"[dro:n]"},{"type":"text","text":"careworn, gaunt, haggard, wan, worn"},{"type":"entry","text":"compact","headword":"compact"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj坚实的（dense，solid）：简洁的（not diffuse or wordy)n.合同，协议（an"},{"type":"text","text":"['ka:mpaekt]"},{"type":"text","text":"agreement or covenant between two or more parties)"},{"type":"note","text":"图词根记忆：com（加强）+pact（合同）→合同"},{"type":"entry","text":"fiscal","headword":"fiscal"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 国库的(relating to public treasury or revenues); 财政的(financial)"},{"type":"text","text":"['fiskl]"},{"type":"note","text":"图词根记忆：fisc（国库）+al→国库的；财政的"},{"type":"entry","text":"medieval","headword":"medieval"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 中世纪的，中古的(of the Middle Ages)"},{"type":"text","text":"[medi'i:v]"},{"type":"note","text":"图词根记忆：medi(中间)+ev(时代)+al→中世纪的"},{"type":"text","text":"the medlieval period 中世纪时期"},{"type":"entry","text":"spectacular","headword":"spectacular"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj壮观的，引|人入胜的(striking, sensational)"},{"type":"text","text":"[spek'taekjalar]"},{"type":"text","text":"图来自spectacle（n.奇观，壮观）"}]},{"number":219,"blocks":[{"type":"text","text":"<K<GRE词汇精选乱序版"},{"type":"entry","text":"bare","headword":"bare"},{"type":"definition","text":"v. 暴雷(to make or lay bare; uncover) adj. 赤裸的(without"},{"type":"text","text":"[ber]"},{"type":"text","text":"clothing)"},{"type":"text","text":"哇！"},{"type":"note","text":"联想记忆：和bear（n.熊）一起记"},{"type":"text","text":"我衣服呢？"},{"type":"text","text":".旋转（to move round and round）：纺纱（to draw out andVz"},{"type":"entry","text":"expeditious","headword":"expeditious"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.迅速的，敏捷的（prompt,quick)"},{"type":"text","text":"bare"},{"type":"text","text":"[ekspa'drfas]"},{"type":"text","text":"图来自expedite（v使加速，促进）"},{"type":"text","text":"expeditiously（adv迅速地，敏捷地）"},{"type":"entry","text":"valedictory","headword":"valedictory"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 告别的，离别的(used in saying goodbye)"},{"type":"text","text":"[vaelr'drktari]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：vale（再见）+dict(说）+ory→告别的"},{"type":"text","text":"The valecictory address, as it has developed in American colleges and"},{"type":"text","text":"universities over the years, has become a very strict form, a literary genre that"},{"type":"text","text":"permits very little deviation."},{"type":"entry","text":"mores","headword":"mores"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 习俗,惯例(the fixed morally binding customs of a particular group)"},{"type":"text","text":"['mo:re1z]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：mor（道德）+es→习俗，惯例"},{"type":"entry","text":"disposed","headword":"disposed"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj愿意的，想干的(inclined)"},{"type":"text","text":"[dt'spauzd]"},{"type":"text","text":"园来自dispose（v使倾向于：处理）"},{"type":"text","text":"It is said that the custom of shaking hands originated when primitive men held"},{"type":"text","text":"out empty hands to indlicate that they had no concealed weapons and were thus"},{"type":"text","text":"amicably dlisposed."},{"type":"entry","text":"signify","headword":"signify"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.表示(to be a sign of)：有重要性(to have significance)"},{"type":"text","text":"['signrfax]"},{"type":"note","text":"园词根记忆：sign（记号）+ily→用记号表示→表示"},{"type":"entry","text":"vantage","headword":"vantage"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.优势，有利地位（superiority in a contest)"},{"type":"text","text":"['vaentrd3]"},{"type":"text","text":"vantage point（观察事物的）有利地点"},{"type":"entry","text":"underlying","headword":"underlying"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj在下面的：根本的：潜在的"},{"type":"text","text":"[Andar'larrn]"},{"type":"text","text":"图组合词：under(在-下面）+lying（鳞着的）→在下面躺着的→在下面的；潜在的"},{"type":"text","text":"Despite the apparently bewildering complexity of this procedure, the"},{"type":"text","text":"unoferlying principle is quite elementary."},{"type":"entry","text":"interrupt","headword":"interrupt"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.暂时中上(to break the continuity of sth. temporarily);打断，打扰(to stop sb."},{"type":"text","text":"[xnta'rapt]"},{"type":"text","text":"speaking or causing some other sort of disturbance)"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：inter（在·之间）+rupt(断裂）→在中间断裂→暂时中止；打断"},{"type":"entry","text":"advent","headword":"advent"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.到来，来临（coming or arrival)"},{"type":"text","text":"['aedvent]"},{"type":"text","text":"围词根记忆：ad（表加强）+vent(到来）→到来"},{"type":"entry","text":"sanity","headword":"sanity"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.头脑清楚，精神健全（soundness of mind and judgement)"},{"type":"text","text":"['saenati]"}]},{"number":220,"blocks":[{"type":"title","text":"Word List 18 >>>"},{"type":"entry","text":"aerial","headword":"aerial"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 空中的, 空气的(of, relating to, or occurring in the air or atmosphere)"},{"type":"text","text":"['erial]"},{"type":"note","text":"园词根记忆：aer(空气）+ial(的）→空中的"},{"type":"entry","text":"charity","headword":"charity"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 慈善(benevolence): 施舍(a voluntary giving of money)"},{"type":"text","text":"['t[aerati]"},{"type":"note","text":"圆联想记忆：cha（音似：茶）+rity→请喝茶→施舍"},{"type":"entry","text":"monsoon","headword":"monsoon"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 季风(a wind system that influences large climatic regions and reverses"},{"type":"text","text":"[ma:n'su:n]"},{"type":"text","text":"direction seasonally);雨季"},{"type":"entry","text":"misrepresentation","headword":"misrepresentation"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.误传，不实的陈述"},{"type":"text","text":"[,ms,reprizen’tex[n]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：mis（错的）+represent（表达）+ation→错误的表达→误传"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 无名，匿名(the quality or state of being anonymous)"},{"type":"entry","text":"anonymity","headword":"anonymity"},{"type":"text","text":"[ana'nrmati]"},{"type":"note","text":"图词根记忆：an（没有）+onym（名称）+ity→无名，匿名"},{"type":"entry","text":"coagulate","headword":"coagulate"},{"type":"definition","text":"v使凝结(to curdle; clot)"},{"type":"text","text":"[kau'aegjulert]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：co（共同）+ag（做）+ulate→一起做→使凝结"},{"type":"text","text":"coagulation (n.凝结）"},{"type":"entry","text":"hallow","headword":"hallow"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.把视为神圣(to make or set apart as holy);尊敬，敬畏(to respect or honor"},{"type":"text","text":"[haelau]"},{"type":"text","text":"greatly: revere)"},{"type":"text","text":"国注意不要和hollow（adj.空润的）相混"},{"type":"text","text":"图hallowed (adlj. 神圣的)"},{"type":"entry","text":"trivia","headword":"trivia"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.琐事，小事（trivial facts or details)"},{"type":"text","text":"['trrvia]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：tri（三）+via（路）→古罗马时的妇女们常在三岔路口谈论一些琐事，引"},{"type":"text","text":"申为“琐事”→琐事"},{"type":"entry","text":"fake","headword":"fake"},{"type":"definition","text":"v. 造(to make seem real by any sort of deception or"},{"type":"text","text":"[ferk]"},{"type":"text","text":"tampering); 伴装(to practice deception by simulating)"},{"type":"text","text":"adf.假的"},{"type":"text","text":"国联想记忆：严惩造（make）假（fake）"},{"type":"entry","text":"ebullience","headword":"ebullience"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.（感情等的）奔放，兴高采烈（high spirits;exuberance）："},{"typ